section.section:
"State share of LEP funding" means:
0.29 in fiscal year 2004;
0.37 in fiscal year 2005;
0.41 in fiscal year 2006;
0.46 in fiscal year 2007; and
0.50 in fiscal year 2008 and each fiscal year thereafter.

For fiscal years 2004 through 2007, the amount of the Tier I LEP grant distributed to a county board shall be equal to the result obtained by multiplying $1,350 by the county's LEP enrollment count, and multiplying this product by:
1.0 for fiscal year 2004;
0.75 for fiscal year 2005;
0.50 for fiscal year 2006; and
0.25 for fiscal year 2007.

For purposes of paragraph (1) of this subsection, the minimum Tier II LEP grant amount for each county is the result obtained by multiplying the Tier II LEP per pupil amount by the county's LEP enrollment count, and multiplying this product by:
0.50 for fiscal year 2004;
0.66 for fiscal year 2005;
0.70 for fiscal year 2006;
0.76 for fiscal year 2007; and
0.80 for fiscal year 2008 and each fiscal year thereafter.
